# No Single-Letter Variables

Do not use single letters for variable names. Use descriptive names so variables are easy to follow across methods and files.

## Examples

**❌ Avoid:**
```javascript
const e = await api.getExecution(orgId, programId, pipelineId, executionId);
executions.forEach(e => { ... });
const p = pipelinePhases.find(...);
const s = stepStates[i];
```

**✅ Prefer:**
```javascript
const execution = await api.getExecution(orgId, programId, pipelineId, executionId);
executions.forEach(execution => { ... });
const phase = pipelinePhases.find(...);
const stepState = stepStates[i];
```

## Exceptions

- Loop indices: `i`, `j`, `k` for simple numeric loops (e.g. `for (let i = 0; i < length; i++)`) are acceptable when the loop body is short and the index is not passed around
- Mathematical notation: single letters in formulas (e.g. `x`, `y` in coordinate math) may be acceptable in isolated calculations
